  "instructions": "The future tense is full of nasal sounds. When you say 'Jaunga' (I will go), the 'un' is nasalized, bleeding into the 'ga'. Additionally, you must practice speaking the root verb + raha + hoon as one smooth rhythm.",
  "targetPhrasesOrWords": [
